You are a senior backend engineer building a production-ready system.

Build a complete backend for a platform called "SaathiLearn" — an AI-powered student learning companion.

Tech Stack:
- Node.js
- Express.js
- PostgreSQL
- Prisma ORM (preferred)
- JWT Authentication
- Socket.io (for real-time mentor updates)

System must be modular, scalable, and clean.

-----------------------------------
CORE FEATURES TO IMPLEMENT
-----------------------------------

1. AUTH SYSTEM
- Signup/Login (JWT-based)
- Roles: student, mentor, admin
- Secure password hashing (bcrypt)

2. STUDENT SYSTEM
- Fetch today's mission
- Track progress (questions completed)
- XP system
- Streak system (daily consistency logic)

3. MISSION ENGINE
- Missions mapped to:
  - class (1–12)
  - subject
  - topic
- Each mission contains:
  - multiple questions
  - difficulty level
- API:
  - GET /mission/today
  - POST /mission/submit

4. GET UNSTUCK SYSTEM
- Step 1: AI Hint API
  - POST /ai/hint
  - returns structured hint
- Step 2: Mentor escalation
  - POST /mentor/request
  - stores request

5. MENTOR SYSTEM
- Mentor dashboard APIs:
  - GET /mentor/students
  - GET /mentor/requests
  - POST /mentor/reply
- Real-time updates using Socket.io

6. NGO DASHBOARD
- Metrics APIs:
  - Engagement Score
  - Consistency Index
  - Learning Improvement
  - At-Risk Students detection

7. OFFLINE SYNC SUPPORT
- Accept batch updates from frontend
- Sync endpoint:
  - POST /sync

